data.name: RenameSymbolPrompt

data.name: DontKnowHowToRunProfile_2
data.value: The project doesn't know how to run the profile with name '{0}' and command '{1}'.
data.comment: {0} is the profile name, which comes from the user. {1} is the profile command, which is usually an internal string but is helpful when diagnosing issues here.

data.name: ErrorInProfilesFile

data.name: ProjectNotRunnableDirectly
data.value:
A project with an Output Type of Class Library cannot be started directly.
In order to debug this project, add an executable project to this solution which references the library project. Set the executable project as the startup project.

data.value: Hot Reload is not available because startup hooks have been disabled, possibly due to trimming.

data.name: IncrementalBuildFailureWarningMessage_2
data.value: WARNING: Potential build performance issue in '{0}'. The project does not appear up-to-date after a successful build: {1}. See https://aka.ms/incremental-build-failure.
data.comment: {0} is the file name of the project. {1} is a description of the failure. The period '.' after {1} is intentional and should be kept.

data.name: WPFApp_Xaml_CouldntFindRootElement_1
data.value: Could not find the expected root element "{0}" in the application definition file.

data.name: WPFApp_Xaml_UnexpectedFormat_2
data.value: The .xaml file was in an unexpected format, near line {0} column {1}.
data.comment: {0} is the line number of the problematic XAML, and {1} is the column.

data.name: InfoBarMessageNuGetCycleDetected
data.value: A circular dependency A -> B -> A was detected during NuGet Restore which caused NuGet to stop restoring. Because the NuGet restore didn't finish correctly, the project might be in a bad state.
